    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Installation - Installing the Rocker Arm Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Installing the Rocker Arm Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place valve bridges across each set of valves. These should be marked if removed. The
                recessed holes set over the valve stems.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650564" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH08/H08026.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="448px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rocker arm orientation</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align rocker arm assembly with bolts over mounting holes and thread hand tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650565" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH08/H08039.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="484px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rocker arm torque sequence</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque bolts in two passes in the sequence illustrated above and to the specified value.
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Torque rocker arm clamp assembly bolts to 27 N&#183;m (20 lbf&#183;ft) for the first
                    pass.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Torque rocker arm clamp assembly bolts to 37 N&#183;m (27 lbf&#183;ft) for the final
                    pass.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
